Get the name of the element containing the data for the current object.

Source: R/class-PKNCAconc.R, R/class-PKNCAdata.R, R/class-PKNCAdose.R, and 2 more
getDataName.Rd

Get the name of the element containing the data for the current object.

# S3 method for PKNCAconc
getDataName(object)

# S3 method for PKNCAdata
getDataName(object)

# S3 method for PKNCAdose
getDataName(object)

# S3 method for PKNCAresults
getDataName(object)

getDataName(object)

# S3 method for default
getDataName(object)

Arguments

object

The object to get the data name from.

Value

A character scalar with the name of the data object (or NULL if the method does not apply).

Methods (by class)

  • default: If no data name exists, returns NULL.

See also

Other PKNCA object extractors: getDepVar(), getIndepVar()
